main event: A ground observer in Taipei reported seeing a bright small object in the atmosphere traveling from north to south at high speed.
interesting points: The object was reported to be moving about four times faster than a satellite seen a few nights prior., The altitude of the object was as high as that of satellites., The exact nature of the object was deemed insufficient for evaluation., The observation was made visually by a civilian observer., The date of the sighting was 10 October 1965.
sighted object: a bright small object in the atmosphere
